name: Ampharos
AbilityText: After your opponent plays a Supporter card from his or her hand, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokemon. You can't use more than 1 Jamming Poke-Body each turn.
Attack1Text: You may discard all Lightning Energy attached to Ampharos. If you do, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any Energy cards attached to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Blastoise
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach as many basic Water Energy cards from your hand to any of your Pokemon in any way you like. If you do, your turn ends. This power can't be used if Blastoise is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Blastoise but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost. You can't add more than 40 damage in this way.

name: Charizard
AbilityText: If your opponent has 3 or less Prize cards left, each of Charizard's attacks does 50 more damage to the Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard 2 Energy cards attached to Charizard. If tails, discard 4 Energy cards attached to Charizard. (If you can't, this attack does nothing.)

name: Entei
AbilityText: Whenever 1 of your opponent's Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from Entei's attacks, discard the top 3 cards from your opponent's deck.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) Flip a coin. If tails, discard 2 Fire Energy attached to Entei.

name: Flygon
AbilityText: As long as Flygon is your Active Pokemon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Active Pokemon between turns, excluding Fighting Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If you attach a Fighting Energy card from your hand to Flygon during this turn, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Gallade
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on the Defending Pokemon until it is 50 HP away from being Knocked Out. If you do, your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: You may choose as many of your face-down Prize cards as you like and put them face up. If you do, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage for each Prize card you chose. (These cards remain face up for the rest of the game.)

name: Gardevoir
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your opponent's discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this power. (The Supporter card remains in your opponent's discard pile.) You can't use more than 1 Telepass Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, your opponent can't use any Poke-Powers on his or her Pokemon.

name: Gastrodon East Sea
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Gastrodon West Sea in play, you may move up to 3 damage counters from Gastrodon East Sea to 1 of your Gastrodon West Sea.
Attack1Text: Does 80 damage minus 10 damage for each damage counter on Gastrodon East Sea.

name: Gastrodon West Sea
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Gastrodon West Sea. Then, remove 2 damage counters from Gastrodon West Sea.
Attack2Text: Put 1 damage counter on each Benched Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Ho-Oh
AbilityText: Once during your opponent's turn, if Ho-Oh would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may flip a coin. If heads, Ho-Oh isn't discarded. Instead, remove all damage counters, Special Conditions, and other effects from Ho-Oh. Then, discard all cards attached to Ho-Oh (except for Energy cards). This counts as Ho-Oh being Knocked Out and your opponent takes a Prize card.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of different types of basic Energy cards attached to Ho-Oh.

name: Jumpluff
AbilityText: Whenever Jumpluff would be damaged by your opponent's attack, flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Jumpluff by that attack.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. For each heads, this attack does 30 damage to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Lickilicky
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. If you choose a Benched Pokemon, switch the Defending Pokemon with that Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to the Pokemon you chose. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, Lickilicky can't attack.

name: Ludicolo
AbilityText: At any time between turns, remove 1 damage counter from Ludicolo.
Attack1Text: If you have a Stadium Card in play, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage. If your opponent has a Stadium card in play, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Lugia
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon and return it to your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon has any Energy cards attached to it, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 120.

name: Mew
Attack1Text: If you have less cards in your hand than your opponent, draw cards until you have the same number of cards as your opponent. (If you have more or the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, this attack does nothing.)
Attack2Text: Choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon in his or her discard pile. Re-creation copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Mew performs that attack.

name: Raikou
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you attach a Lightning Energy card from your hand to Raikou, you may put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Discard 3 cards from the top of your deck. This attack does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each Lightning Energy card you discarded. Then, attach those Lightning Energy cards to 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Roserade
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage and remove 3 damage counters from Roserade.

name: Salamence
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 basic Fire Energy cards or 2 basic Water Energy cards attached to Salamence. If you discarded 2 basic Fire Energy cards, this attack does 100 damage to the Defending Pokemon. If you discarded 2 Basic Water Energy cards, this attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) (If you can't discard cards, this attack does nothing.)

name: Suicune
AbilityText: Once during your turn, when you put Suicune from your hand onto your Bench, you may search your discard pile for up to 3 Water Pokemon, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Venusaur
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, choose either Asleep, Burned, or Poisoned. The Defending Pokemon is now affected by that Special Condition. This power can't be used if Venusaur is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove 4 damage counters from Venusaur.

name: Absol
Attack1Text: Choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it. If you discarded a Trainer, Supporter, or Stadium card, choose 1 more card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.
Attack2Text: If you played Absol from your hand during this turn, this attack's base damage is 40 instead of 10.

name: Arcanine
AbilityText: Once during your turn, when you play Arcanine from your hand to evolve 1 of your Benched Pokemon, you may switch Arcanine with 1 of your Active Pokemon. If you do, you may move any number of Energy cards attached to that Pokemon to Arcanine.
Attack1Text: Arcanine does 40 damage to itself.

name: Banette
Attack1Text: Put as many damage counters as you like on Banette. (You can't put more than Banette's remaining HP.) Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If Banette is in your discard pile, this attack does 40 damage plus 40 more damage, then search your discard pile for Banette, show it to your opponent, and shuffle it into your deck.

name: Dugtrio
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Dugtrio during your opponent's next turn. If Dugtrio is your Active Pokemon at the end of your opponent's next turn, put 6 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent flips a coin. If tails, this attack does 50 damage plus 50 more damage.

name: Electivire
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to Electivire. This power can't be used if Electivire is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Discard all Lightning Energy attached to Electivire. Flip a coin for each Lightning Energy you discarded. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.

name: Electrode
AbilityText: Once during your turn, if Electrode would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, you may use this power. Electrode isn't discarded. Instead, attach it as an Energy card to 1 of your Pokemon. While attached, this card is a Special Energy card and provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time. (Has no effect other than providing Energy.)
Attack1Text: You may do 40 damage plus 60 more damage. If you do, Electrode does 100 damage to itself.

name: Furret
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: You may switch Furret with 1 of your Benched Pokemon. If you do, move as many Energy cards attached to Furret as you like to the new Active Pokemon.

name: Golduck
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokemon's attacks. That Pokemon can use only that attack during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: You may do 40 damage plus 20 more damage. If you do, Golduck is now Confused.

name: Golem
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 30 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: You may do 40 damage instead of 80 to the Defending Pokemon. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Golem by attacks is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Jynx
Attack1Text: If Jynx was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Move 2 damage counters from Jynx to the Defending Pokemon. If Smoochum is anywhere under Jynx, move 4 damage counters instead.

name: Magmortar
AbilityText: When you attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to Magmortar, remove 2 damage counters from Magmortar.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage times the number of Fire Energy attached to Magmortar.
Attack2Text: Does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Minun
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any Pokemon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, you may draw 2 cards. You can't use more than 1 Minus Charge Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Minun is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: If you have Plusle on your Bench, you may move an Energy card attached to Minun to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Mothim
Attack1Text: During your next turn, if an attack does damage to the Defending Pokemon (after applying Weakness and Resistance), that attack does 40 more damage.
Attack2Text: If Mothim has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 damage plus 40 more damage.

name: Nidoking
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. Before doing damage, you may switch 1 of the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. The new Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Nidoqueen on your Bench. This attack does 60 damage plus 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Pidgeot
Attack1Text: If Pidgeot was damaged by an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does the same amount of damage done to Pidgeot to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Plusle
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if any of your Pokemon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn, you may search your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. You can't use more than 1 Plus Charge Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Plusle is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: If you have Minun on your Bench, you may do 20 damage to any 1 Benched Pokemon instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Sharpedo
AbilityText: If Sharpedo is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Sharpedo is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon has 2 or more damage counters on it, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage. This attack damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokemon.

name: Sunflora
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 1 damage counter from each of your Grass Pokemon. You can't use more than 1 Grass Whistle Poke-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Sunflora is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage times the number of heads. If you get 2 or more heads, Sunflora is now Confused.

name: Unown [S]
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown S, Unown E, and Unown T on your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Weavile
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may use this power. Each of your Active Pokemon's type is Darkness until the end of your turn. If that Pokemon is no longer your Active Pokemon, this effect ends.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Darkness Energy cards and attach them to any of your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has 6 or more cards in his or her hand, discard a number of cards without looking until your opponent has 5 cards left in his or her hand.

name: Wormadam Plant Cloak
AbilityText: If Wormadam Plant Cloak has 2 or more Grass Energy attached to it, Wormadam Plant Cloak gets +40 HP.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon has fewer remaining HP than Wormadam Plant Cloak, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Wormadam Sandy Cloak
AbilityText: Prevent all effects of attacks, excluding damage, done to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.
Attack1Text: Does 40 damage plus 10 damage for each Fighting Energy attached to Wormadam Sandy Cloak.

name: Wormadam Trash Cloak
AbilityText: If Wormadam Trash Cloak has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, any damage done to Wormadam Trash Cloak by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Wormadam Trash Cloak does 20 damage to itself.

name: Xatu
AbilityText: Once during your turn, if Xatu is on your Bench, you may choose 1 Special Condition from 1 of your Active Pokemon and remove that Special Condition. Then, 1 of the Defending Pokemon is now affected by that Special Condition that you chose.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to that Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Breloom
Attack1Text: Remove from Breloom a number of damage counters equal to the amount of Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon's Retreat Cost is 0, this attack does 60 damage plus 60 more damage.

name: Charmeleon
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard a Fire Energy attached to Charmeleon and this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Cloyster
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to Cloyster by attacks during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. For each heads, choose an opponent's Pokemon in play and this attack does 20 damage to those Pokemon. (You may choose the same Pokemon more than once.) (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Donphan
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon, if any. You switch Donphan with 1 of your Benched Pokemon, if any.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon has a Pokemon Tool card attached to it, this attack does 70 damage plus 60 more damage.

name: Farfetch'd
Attack1Text: During your next turn, Farfetch'd's Leek Slap attack's base damage is 60.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, Farfetch'd can't use Leek Slap.

name: Flaaffy
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Lightning Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokemon. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, Flaaffy does 10 damage to itself.

name: Ivysaur
Attack1Text: Remove 1 damage counter from Ivysaur.

name: Kecleon
AbilityText: If any basic Energy card attached to Kecleon is the same as the Attacking Pokemon's type, any damage done by attacks from the Pokemon to Kecleon is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does no damage to the Defending Pokemon. Instead, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Kirlia
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for a Supporter card and use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack. (The Supporter card remains in your discard pile.)
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Lombre
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from his or her hand during his or her next turn.
Attack2Text: Remove 2 damage counters from Lombre.

name: Miltank
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, remove 3 damage counters from 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Muk
AbilityText: At the end of each player's turn, each of your opponent's Active Pokemon that has any Grass Energy attached to it is now Poisoned. If that Pokemon is already Poisoned, Toxic Sludge Poke-Body does nothing to that Pokemon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Confused and can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Nidorino
Attack1Text: During your next turn, each of Nidorino's attacks does 20 more damage to the Defending Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Pidgeotto
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Pinsir
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack's base damage is 10 instead of 100.

name: Quagsire
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Quagsire is your Active Pokemon and the Defending Pokemon has any Water Energy attached to it, you may remove 3 damage counters from Quagsire.
Attack1Text: Does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Raticate
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 60 more damage.
Attack2Text: If Raticate has any Darkness Energy attached to it, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Roselia
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Sableye
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck. Choose as many Trainer cards as you like, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Put the other cards back on top of your deck. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If you and your opponent have a different number of Prize cards left, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Shelgon
Attack1Text: During your next turn, Shelgon's Protect Charge attack's base damage is 80.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Shelgon by attacks is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Skiploom
AbilityText: If Skiploom has any Grass Energy attached to it, any damage done to Skiploom by attacks from your opponent's Evolved Pokemon is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Switch Skiploom with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Smeargle
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards, show them to your opponent, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose an attack on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. Trace copies that attack except for its Energy cost. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.) Smeargle performs that attack.

name: Smoochum
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Jynx from your hand onto Smoochum (this counts as evolving Smoochum) and remove all damage counters from Smoochum.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Energy card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

name: Unown [K]
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 2 damage counters from 1 of the Defending Pokemon.

name: Unown [N]
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if you have Unown N, Unown O, and Unown D on your Bench, you may ask your opponent to take a Prize card. If he or she does, you take a Prize card. If he or she doesn't, draw a card.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Unown [O]

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Unown [X]

Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Unown [Z]
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown Z is on your Bench and you have no cards in your deck, you may discard all cards attached to Unown Z and put Unown Z on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Remove as many damage counters as you like from each Unown you have in play. Put that many damage counters on the Defending Pokemon.

name: Venomoth
AbilityText: If Venomoth is your Active Pokemon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if Venomoth is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.
Attack1Text: Prevent all effects of an attack, excluding damage, done to Venomoth during your opponent's next turn.

name: Vibrava
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Wartortle
Attack1Text: Wartortle can't use Giant Wave during your next turn.

name: Bagon
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on Bagon.

name: Bulbasaur
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Burmy Plant Cloak
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Plant Cloak is your Active Pokemon, you may search your discard pile for a basic Grass Energy card and attach it to Burmy Plant Cloak.
Attack1Text: If Burmy Plant Cloak has any Grass Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Burmy Sandy Cloak
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Sandy Cloak is your Active Pokemon, you may search your discard for a basic Fighting Energy card and attach it to Burmy Sandy Cloak.
Attack1Text: If Burmy Sandy Cloak has any Fighting Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Burmy Trash Cloak
AbilityText: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Burmy Trash Cloak is your Active Pokemon, you may search your discard for a basic Metal Energy card and attach it to Burmy Trash Cloak.
Attack1Text: If Burmy Trash Cloak has any Metal Energy attached to it, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Carvanha
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a card from your opponent's hand without looking and discard it.

name: Charmander
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Clefairy
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Corsola
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 different types of Basic Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Diglett
Attack1Text: Draw a card from the bottom of your deck.

name: Duskull
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.

name: Electabuzz
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, Electabuzz does 30 damage to itself.

name: Grimer
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

name: Growlithe
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Hoppip

name: Lickitung
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Lotad
Attack1Text: If Lotad has less Energy attached to it than the Defending Pokemon, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Magmar
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Mareep
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Murkrow
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness, Resistance, Poke-Powers, Poke-Bodies, or any other effects on that Pokemon.

name: Natu
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokemon.

name: Nidoran ♂
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Phanpy
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Phanpy.
Attack2Text: Phanpy does 10 damage to itself.

name: Pidgey
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokemon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Psyduck
Attack1Text: If Psyduck is Confused, draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused. If tails, Psyduck is now Confused.

name: Qwilfish
AbilityText: Once during your opponent's turn, if Qwilfish is your Active Pokemon and is damage by an attack (even if Qwilfish is Knocked Out), you may flip a coin. If heads, the Attacking Pokemon is now Poisoned. Put 2 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokemon between turns.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Ralts

name: Shellos West Sea
Attack2Text: Discard a Water Energy attached to Shellos West Sea and remove all damage counters from Shellos West Sea.

name: Shroomish
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Shuckle
AbilityText: Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to Shuckle by your opponent's Pokemon that has any Special Energy cards attached to it.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Poisoned. As long as the Defending Pokemon remains Poisoned by this attack, it can't use any Poke-Body.

name: Shuppet
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Spinda
Attack1Text: Draw a card from the top and the bottom of your deck.
Attack2Text: If any basic Energy card attached to Spinda is the same type as any Energy attached to the Defending Pokemon, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Squirtle
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Water Energy attached to Squirtle. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each heads.

name: Stantler
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon isn't an Evolved Pokemon, that Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Sunkern
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, remove all damage counters from Sunkern, search your deck for an Evolution card that evolves from Sunkern, and put it onto Sunkern. (This counts as evolving Sunkern.) Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Trapinch
Attack1Text: Switch the Defending Pokemon with 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokemon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Venonat
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Voltorb
Attack2Text: Voltorb does 50 damage to itself.

name: Wooper
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokemon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.
